.TH "ext4_should_retry_alloc" 9 "ext4_should_retry_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ext4_should_retry_alloc \- check if a block allocation should be retried
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ext4_should_retry_alloc
.BI "(struct super_block *sb "  ","
.BI "int *retries "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sb" 12
superblock
.IP "retries" 12
number of retry attempts made so far
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBext4_should_retry_alloc\fP is called when ENOSPC is returned while
attempting to allocate blocks.  If there's an indication that a pending
journal transaction might free some space and allow another attempt to
succeed, this function will wait for the current or committing transaction
to complete and then return TRUE.
